The death toll at the site of the collapsed three-storey building in the Yaba area of Lagos rose to five on Sunday. The bodies of the deceased persons were recovered from the rubble of the building, which was under construction when it collapsed on Saturday.  One of the lifeless bodies recovered on Sunday was that of a student on industrial training, pushing the death toll to five. As at Saturday night, three persons had been confirmed dead. Two persons have been rescued alive, the Lagos State Emergency Management Agency Public Relations Officer, Okunbor Nosa said. The incident happened on Akanbi Crescent, close to the University of Lagos.



